#title: Next.js 13 to 15 Migration Skill
#author: AIF Migration Team

@skill[name="nextjs-13-to-15", version="1.0", profile=migration]
  @precondition
    Repository uses Next.js 13.x with React 18.
    Project uses the App Router (app/ directory).
    Package manager is npm or yarn.
    TypeScript configuration present (tsconfig.json).
    No custom server.js overriding the Next.js server.

  @step[order=1]
    Upgrade core dependencies in package.json:
    - next: ^13.x.x → ^15.0.0
    - react: ^18.x.x → ^19.0.0
    - react-dom: ^18.x.x → ^19.0.0
    - @types/react: ^18.x.x → ^19.0.0
    - @types/react-dom: ^18.x.x → ^19.0.0
    Remove deprecated peer dependencies:
    - @next/font (now built into next/font)

  @step[order=2]
    Migrate async request APIs. In Next.js 15, params, searchParams,
    headers(), cookies(), and draftMode() are now async.

    Before:
      export default function Page({ params }) {
        const { slug } = params;
      }

    After:
      export default async function Page({ params }) {
        const { slug } = await params;
      }

    Apply to all page.tsx, layout.tsx, route.tsx, and
    generateMetadata functions. Both server and client components
    that access these APIs must be updated.

  @step[order=3]
    Update next.config.js to next.config.ts (optional but recommended).
    Migrate deprecated configuration options:
    - Remove experimental.serverActions (now stable, enabled by default)
    - Remove experimental.appDir (stable since Next 13.4)
    - Update images.domains to images.remotePatterns format
    - Replace experimental.instrumentationHook with instrumentation (top-level)
    - Remove swcMinify (now default behavior)

  @step[order=4]
    Update caching semantics. Next.js 15 changed default caching behavior:
    - fetch() requests are no longer cached by default
    - Route Handlers (GET) are no longer cached by default
    - Client-side router cache no longer caches Page components by default

    Add explicit cache directives where caching was relied upon:
    - fetch(url, { cache: 'force-cache' }) for previously cached fetches
    - export const dynamic = 'force-static' for static route handlers
    - Use <Link prefetch={true}> for routes that benefit from prefetching

  @step[order=5]
    Update middleware and edge runtime patterns:
    - NextRequest geo and ip properties are removed; use provider-specific headers
    - Replace runtime = 'experimental-edge' with runtime = 'edge'
    - Update Middleware matcher patterns if using deprecated syntax

  @step[order=6]
    Update React 19 patterns in client components:
    - Replace useEffect for data fetching with React.use() where appropriate
    - Replace forwardRef with direct ref prop on function components
    - Update Context.Provider to direct Context usage: <Context value={...}>
    - Remove deprecated string refs if any remain

  @step[order=7]
    Update testing infrastructure:
    - Update @testing-library/react to latest (supports React 19)
    - Update jest or vitest configuration for Next 15 transforms
    - Replace deprecated renderHook import location
    - Update MSW or similar mocking tools if they depend on fetch behavior

  @verify
    No remaining `@next/font` imports in source files.
    No remaining `experimental.serverActions` in next config.
    No remaining `experimental.appDir` in next config.
    All `params` and `searchParams` access uses `await`.
    All files import from `next/font` not `@next/font`.
    No remaining `runtime = 'experimental-edge'` declarations.
    No remaining `forwardRef` usage without migration comment.
    Package.json shows `next` version >= 15.0.0.
    Package.json shows `react` version >= 19.0.0.

  @fallback
    If a component uses complex params destructuring in server components,
    preserve the original and flag for manual review.

    If a custom caching wrapper relies on Next.js implicit caching behavior,
    flag it for manual review with a note explaining the caching change.

    If third-party packages depend on Next.js 13 internals (e.g., custom
    server adapters or internal routing APIs), skip those files and list
    them as requiring package upgrades before migration can proceed.

  @example
    Before (Next.js 13 page component):
      export default function UserPage({ params }) {
        const { id } = params;
        return <div>User {id}</div>;
      }

    After (Next.js 15 page component):
      export default async function UserPage({ params }) {
        const { id } = await params;
        return <div>User {id}</div>;
      }

    Before (Next.js 13 cached fetch):
      const data = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data');

    After (Next.js 15 explicit cache):
      const data = await fetch('https://api.example.com/data', { cache: 'force-cache' });

  @decision
    If a file uses both Pages Router (`getServerSideProps`) and App Router
    patterns, skip the file entirely — mixed paradigms require manual migration.

    If a client component uses `useEffect` for simple data fetching and the
    component tree supports Suspense, prefer migrating to `React.use()`.
    Otherwise, keep `useEffect` as-is.

    If `next.config.js` has complex plugin chains (e.g., `withBundleAnalyzer`,
    `withPWA`), convert to `next.config.ts` only if all plugins support TS config.
    Otherwise, keep `.js` and only update the deprecated options.

  @red_flag
    Do not migrate files that import from Next.js internal modules
    (paths starting with `next/dist/`). These are private APIs and
    require manual assessment before migration.

    Do not automatically convert `getServerSideProps` or `getStaticProps`
    in pages/ directory files — these are Pages Router patterns and
    require a separate Pages→App Router migration, not a version upgrade.

  @output_contract
    All source files migrated to Next.js 15 API surface.
    Build succeeds with `next build`.
    No TypeScript errors related to API changes.
    All previously passing tests continue to pass.
    Deprecated configuration options removed.
    Caching behavior explicitly specified where previously implicit.
@/skill
